01:00:27,958 --> 01:00:28,959
What's when?

764
01:00:30,502 --> 01:00:32,296
When you were hurt,

765
01:00:33,172 --> 01:00:35,507
Ji-woo must've found out then.

766
01:00:35,591 --> 01:00:37,051
Maybe that's why she left.

767
01:00:40,929 --> 01:00:43,182
Still, she grew up to be a bright person.

768
01:00:43,265 --> 01:00:44,516
Yes.

769
01:00:46,143 --> 01:00:47,436
Should we invite her for dinner?

770
01:00:48,562 --> 01:00:49,772
Kyeong-do will hate it.

771
01:00:51,732 --> 01:00:53,275
- Right?
- Yeah.

772
01:01:09,124 --> 01:01:11,627
You should've told me
that you were coming my house.

773
01:01:11,710 --> 01:01:13,420
I didn't know they invited you too.

774
01:01:14,505 --> 01:01:16,173
A son isn't a guest to invite.

775
01:01:16,256 --> 01:01:18,008
A guest would come when they're invited.

776
01:01:18,967 --> 01:01:20,677
You're normally at the laundromat.

777
01:01:20,761 --> 01:01:23,138
Here. Eat.

778
01:01:23,222 --> 01:01:27,142
Thank you. I absolutely love yukgaejang.

779
01:01:35,818 --> 01:01:36,652
Enjoy.

780
01:01:36,735 --> 01:01:38,612
Yes. Thank you for the food.

781
01:01:53,419 --> 01:01:54,795
Craving soju?

782
01:01:56,296 --> 01:01:59,091
People make that sound
when they have spicy food.

783
01:02:01,885 --> 01:02:06,723
You see, this is the exact taste
that I expected when I first saw it.

784
01:02:06,807 --> 01:02:09,935
You should have opened a restaurant
instead of a laundromat.

785
01:02:14,857 --> 01:02:15,983
Thank you for the food.

786
01:02:19,862 --> 01:02:21,947
Bulgogi too? Thank you.

787
01:02:25,784 --> 01:02:27,536
Can I have this bulgogi too?

788
01:02:28,120 --> 01:02:29,079
As much as you want.

789
01:02:33,667 --> 01:02:34,793
So full. Gosh.

790
01:02:36,378 --> 01:02:37,504
Here.

791
01:02:37,588 --> 01:02:38,922
That was a nice meal.

792
01:02:50,684 --> 01:02:51,518
ON MUTE

793
01:02:52,144 --> 01:02:53,979
- Baseball now?
- Well,

794
01:02:54,062 --> 01:02:55,314
I muted it.

795
01:02:56,023 --> 01:02:58,567
Stop watching baseball.
Now is so not the time.

796
01:03:00,194 --> 01:03:01,195
You see…

797
01:03:01,278 --> 01:03:02,321
What?

798
01:03:03,113 --> 01:03:06,158
Well… in my opinion…

799
01:03:06,992 --> 01:03:10,787
Quitting what you like, whatever it is…

800
01:03:14,166 --> 01:03:15,667
Well… it's crazy tough.

801
01:03:20,005 --> 01:03:23,217
Still, baseball isn't harmful.

802
01:03:23,300 --> 01:03:24,384
That's nice.

803
01:03:26,386 --> 01:03:29,056
It's healthy. It prevents dementia.

804
01:03:29,139 --> 01:03:29,973
Really?

805
01:03:30,807 --> 01:03:31,767
Better than Go-Stop?

806
01:03:31,850 --> 01:03:35,145
Why, Go-Stop has a risk of gambling.

807
01:03:36,355 --> 01:03:38,565
Yes. You're right.

808
01:03:39,691 --> 01:03:42,152
- It's a hit.
- What, really?

809
01:03:42,861 --> 01:03:45,489
What's the point of the other team's hit?

810
01:03:46,698 --> 01:03:48,534
Are you a Hanyeong fan?

811
01:03:49,785 --> 01:03:52,538
Have you seen them losing by 7-nil
then turning it around by 8 to 7?

812
01:03:53,247 --> 01:03:55,290
No. Unfortunately, I missed it.

813
01:03:55,374 --> 01:03:56,750
Do you like baseball?

814
01:03:56,833 --> 01:03:57,668
Kind of.

815
01:04:00,504 --> 01:04:03,006
- We have something in common.
- Of course.

816
01:04:03,090 --> 01:04:04,550
Let me give you a piece of apple.

817
01:04:05,717 --> 01:04:08,428
- I didn't peel it though.
- Thank you.

818
01:04:23,485 --> 01:04:26,530
Maybe if Seo Ji-yeon
was born out of wedlock...

819
01:04:26,613 --> 01:04:29,241
But Seo Ji-woo? And get rid of her?

820
01:04:31,159 --> 01:04:33,203
That won't affect the management.

821
01:04:33,745 --> 01:04:35,497
That's too weak. That won't do it.

822
01:04:35,581 --> 01:04:39,167
A KO isn't the only way to win.
You can also win by decision.

823
01:04:41,295 --> 01:04:44,047
Do you know
what Koreans are most sensitive about?

824
01:04:45,632 --> 01:04:46,633
Affairs.

825
01:04:48,010 --> 01:04:51,847
JARIM's dead Chairman Seo's wife
had an affair.

826
01:04:52,973 --> 01:04:55,309
And her daughter also has an affair.

827
01:05:00,981 --> 01:05:03,692
I think this alley is pretty. It's cozy.

828
01:05:06,903 --> 01:05:10,574
Maybe it's true that a married couple
has similar taste.

829
01:05:10,657 --> 01:05:11,617
You're copying me.

830
01:05:12,200 --> 01:05:13,869
Don't go overboard.

831
01:05:14,494 --> 01:05:15,370
Okay.

832
01:05:16,955 --> 01:05:18,749
I like how it sounds.

833
01:05:18,832 --> 01:05:19,958
Alley.

834
01:05:20,667 --> 01:05:22,002
Alleyway.

835
01:05:22,753 --> 01:05:24,129
Alley captain.

836
01:05:24,838 --> 01:05:25,964
Alley entrance.

837
01:05:29,551 --> 01:05:31,970
You should've stayed in the Culture Team.

838
01:05:38,226 --> 01:05:39,728
You know what?

839
01:05:40,437 --> 01:05:44,399
It feels weird
to have dinner together like this.

840
01:05:45,776 --> 01:05:47,361
Why?

841
01:05:47,986 --> 01:05:50,155
Is it like visiting your in-laws' house?

842
01:05:50,238 --> 01:05:51,490
No.

843
01:05:52,491 --> 01:05:53,742
I mean I like it.

844
01:05:54,910 --> 01:05:55,744
It's nice.

845
01:05:56,995 --> 01:05:59,956
It's like an alley. A cozy alley.

846
01:06:05,337 --> 01:06:08,507
Let's live like this alley.

847
01:06:11,718 --> 01:06:15,055
<i>JARIM's dead Chairman Seo's wife</i>
<i>had an affair.</i>

848
01:06:16,181 --> 01:06:18,600
<i>And her daughter also has an affair.</i>

849
01:06:19,476 --> 01:06:22,479
<i>There will be a boycott of JARIM.</i>

850
01:06:22,562 --> 01:06:26,108
<i>It'll only be a matter of time</i>
<i>until the sisters get kicked out.</i>

851
01:06:26,900 --> 01:06:30,153
<i>And the company will be sold.</i>

852
01:08:24,893 --> 01:08:28,104
<i>So, you are… going?</i>

853
01:08:29,439 --> 01:08:31,608
<i>Don't you know what this field is like?</i>

854
01:08:31,691 --> 01:08:34,069
<i>It's better to hide. We might as well die!</i>

855
01:08:35,320 --> 01:08:36,905
<i>Just go live abroad.</i>

856
01:08:36,988 --> 01:08:38,865
<i>- Director Seo Ji-woo.</i>
<i>- Director Seo,</i>

857
01:08:38,949 --> 01:08:41,576
<i>don't you think that's irresponsible?</i>

858
01:08:43,078 --> 01:08:45,956
<i>Then let her live as an adulteress!</i>

859
01:08:46,915 --> 01:08:49,042
<i>I'm here</i>
<i>because the dog was barking too loud.</i>

860
01:08:49,125 --> 01:08:51,002
Kang Min-woo,
you're out of bullets, right?

861
01:08:51,086 --> 01:08:54,256
<i>I'll go, and if I can't bear it,</i>
<i>I'll come back.</i>

862
01:08:55,757 --> 01:08:58,176
<i>Ji-woo, let's…</i>

863
01:08:59,511 --> 01:09:00,846
live well.
